    {
      "id": "1006278",
      "title": "",
      "description": "Braintree branch riders:\r\nRegular service is operating between JFK/UMass and Braintree, but riders must take a shuttle bus between Broadway and JFK/UMass.\r\n\r\nAccessibility:\r\nFree and accessible shuttle buses are operating between Broadway and Ashmont. Accessible van service is available between Broadway and Ashmont. Riders should see station personnel for assistance.\r\n\r\nTravel times:\r\nRiders using shuttles bus service should budget ample extra travel time. For example, a rider travelling to Park Street from Ashmont should budget at least an additional 30 \u2013 40 minutes of travel in additional to their regular commute.\r\n\r\nAlternate service:\r\nRiders are encouraged to consider Commuter Rail service between South Station and Braintree, which will be free during this service change. Riders arriving and departing from South Station should see Keolis staff for free access through the fare gates. Regular fares should be purchased for travel beyond Braintree.\r\n\r\nShuttle Locations:\r\n\r\nBroadway:\r\nW. Broadway @ Broadway Station\r\n\r\nAndrew:\r\nNorthbound - Dorchester Ave @ Leeds St\r\nSouthbound - Dorchester Ave @ Dexter St\r\n\r\nJFK/UMass:\r\nNorthbound - Inner Busway\r\nSouthbound - Outer Busway\r\n\r\nSavin Hill:\r\nNorthbound - Dorchester Ave @ Savin Hill Ave\r\nSouthbound - Dorchester Ave @ Thornley Rd\r\n\r\nFields Corner:\r\nNorthbound - Dorchester Ave opp Charles St\r\nSouthbound - Dorchester Ave @ Fields Corner Station\r\n\r\nShawmut:\r\nAll shuttles - Dorchester Ave @ Centre St\r\n\r\nAshmont:\r\nAshmont Busway (Berths # 5 & 6)",
      "severity": 7,
      "route_id": "unknown"
    },
    {
      "id": "1001863",
      "title": "",
      "description": "Skipped outbound stops:\r\nOxford St @ Washington St\r\nOxford St @ Market St",
      "severity": 7,
      "route_id": "unknown"
    },
    {
      "id": "1001817",
      "title": "",
      "description": "The escalator will remain out of service for the foreseeable future. This decision was made after a thorough inspection determined that corrosion on the escalator\u2019s steel truss was so severe that it could not be repaired further and that a complete replacement of the escalator would be required. Replacing the escalator at this location requires a more extended unit meeting modern escalator safety requirements. This longer unit will require significant alteration to the station entrance to meet code requirements. The MBTA has currently begun design work to understand what station upgrades will be needed.\r\n\r\nDue to these complexities, we expect the escalator will remain out of service for a significant time. We recognize the challenges this poses to our riders, and please know we are working to identify a solution as quickly as possible. In the meantime, Government Center Station, which is fully accessible and serves the Blue Line, is under a quarter-mile from Bowdoin Station.",
      "severity": 1,
      "route_id": "unknown"
    },
